## Overall Integration Summary

| Script | Key Finding | Narrative Effect | Include? |
|--------|-------------|-----------------|----------|
| A — Deliberation | AI speeds up 5× more than Control (progressive, p<0.001) | New temporal finding: AI reduces processing time via habituation | ✓ Primary |
| C — FDR | Only 3/30 Big5 correlations survive: all Extraversion | Sharpens personality section: one clean predictor | ✓ Primary |
| D — Image populations | Humans succeed on genuinely-wrong AI images (acc=0.661) | Validates cognitive forcing; noisy/genuine split matters | ✓ Primary |
| E — Metacognition | No image-level effect; uncertain = slower (+4.3s) | Null on metacognition; useful process measure | ✓ Supplementary |
| B — Batch | *Not yet run — needs batch variable* | Will determine if Extraversion is confounded by cohort | ⚠ Essential pre-submission |

The **revised narrative** these results enable:

> *"AI assistance produced a robust accuracy improvement confirmed across all participant subsets. Beyond accuracy, AI exposure generated a condition-specific, progressive reduction in decision time — consistent with interface habituation rather than trust shortcuts (which were not found). Among personality predictors, only Extraversion associations survived multiple comparison correction, with higher Extraversion predicting lower AI-assisted accuracy and higher skepticism — an effect that may be partially explained by the shared testing environment. Image-level analysis confirmed that cognitive forcing successfully elicits independent judgment: on images where the AI was incorrect but labels were reliable, human consensus accuracy (0.661) substantially exceeded the AI, demonstrating that the interface does not produce systemic over-reliance."*
